some things that u might wanna add in ur formulas.<br>
1) u can avoid hits completely<br>
2) u take max damage more often than all other values (against uber mobs)<br>
now, u assumed there is a formula that calculates a value X from 1 to 20 which will add a damage interval to a defined base damage. X depends on AC of tank, level of tank, class of tank, attack of mob and level of mob. not that i could tell for sure, but i assume verants formula first calculates a value from negative infinity to positive infinity, after that the numbers smaller than 0 become 0 (0 means miss) and all the numbers larger than 20 become 20 (20 means max hit) and all the numbers between 0 and 20 are rounded to the next integer. this would explain why<br>
1) a decaded skeleton misses a high level so often (many negative numbers, thus rounded up to 0) or why<br>
2) uber mobs hit often for max damage (many numbers larger than 20 and thus rounded down to 20).<br>
verants formula will most likely stay a secret forever. since i wrote many works on technical topics that try to put nature or human behavior into mathematical formulas and i dont know anything better to do right now, i ll show up with a specific formula on this board soon.<br>
